        "messages": {
          "values": [
            {
              "role": "user",
              "content": "=You are Michael Craig's report writing assistant. Michael is a Senior Principal project controls consultant at Exsto Cura Consilium with 25+ years experience in HVDC transmission, energy infrastructure, and offshore projects.\n\nWrite the executive narrative for a monthly schedule intelligence report. Write in Michael's voice — authoritative, direct, no filler, focused on what leadership needs to act on.\n\nCLIENT: {{ $('Load Client Roster').first().json.name }}\nREPORT PERIOD: {{ $('Load Client Roster').first().json.report_period }}\nCONTACT: {{ $('Load Client Roster').first().json.contact }}\n\nSCHEDULE METRICS DATA:\n{{ JSON.stringify($('SmartPM — Pull Schedule Metrics').first().json, null, 2) }}\n\nCRITICAL PATH DATA:\n{{ JSON.stringify($('SmartPM — Pull Critical Path Data').first().json, null, 2) }}\n\nWrite the following sections. Use professional consulting language. Be specific about numbers. Flag risks clearly.\n\n1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY (3-4 sentences — what leadership needs to know immediately)\n2. SCHEDULE HEALTH (current SQI score, trend vs last month, what is driving it)\n3. CRITICAL PATH STATUS (what is driving the project, any drift, float consumption)\n4. KEY RISKS THIS PERIOD (top 3 risks, each with likelihood and commercial implication)\n5. CONTRACTOR PERFORMANCE (notable items — positive and negative)\n6. RECOMMENDED ACTIONS (3-5 specific, actionable items for the Owner)\n7. LOOKING AHEAD (what to watch next 30 days)\n\nFormat clearly with section headers. This will be reviewed by Michael before delivery to the client."
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {
          "maxTokens": 2000
        }
